      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments cover the same pump geometry family, fluid (bovine blood analogue), and operating envelope as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry at the same 5 flow-speed combinations defined in the COU. Bovine blood analogue (glycerol-water, matched viscosity) was used consistently. Validation scope is directly relevant to the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 given assessed discretization error factor covers dominant numerical error sources.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, explicit characterisation of iterative solver residual contributions beyond GCI-based discretization uncertainty is not required. Residuals were monitored to 1e-6 for all equations; no solver divergence or stall was observed. Factor scoped as not-assessed per MRL 2 requirements."
