      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this COU.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment is not required at MRL 2. Simulation setup was performed by an experienced CFD analyst with documented training records. Peer review of boundary condition setup and post-processing scripts was conducted internally."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; model form adequacy is addressed through output comparison factor.",
      "rationale": "Formal model form error quantification is not required at MRL 2. The SST k-ω turbulence model with power-law hemolysis damage accumulation is an established approach for centrifugal pump hemolysis prediction. Model form plausibility is supported by the output comparison results."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters are documented with nominal values and sources; manufacturing tolerances and fluid property variability are incorporated into the UQ analysis.",
      "rationale": "Thirteen model inputs were identified and documented: rotational speed, inlet flow rate, fluid viscosity, density, blood damage coefficients (C, α, β), impeller tip clearance, volute gap, inlet temperature, outlet back-pressure, and wall roughness. Nominal values and sources are recorded in the simulation plan. A comprehensive Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification study was executed, propagating distributions across all 13 inputs through 2000 CFD-surrogate evaluations to characterise output variability. The 95th-percentile RH remains below 1.0, confirming the acceptance criterion is robust to input variability. Input documentation and UQ coverage satisfy the MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for computational model credibility assessment.",
      "rationale": "Physical test sample characterisation beyond what is captured in the test conditions factor is not required at MRL 2. Pump geometry was manufactured to nominal CAD dimensions; dimensional inspection report is on file."
    },
